</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.25IN;">
<B>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	We have a
	substantial amount of indebtedness that could affect our future operations.
</FONT>
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	As of December 31,
	2016, total debt outstanding was $1,056,147,000. We are subject to the risks
	normally associated with debt financing, including the risk that our cash flow
	from operations will be insufficient to meet required debt service. Our debt
	service costs generally will not be reduced if developments at the property,
	such as the entry of new competitors or the loss of major tenants, cause a
	reduction in the income from the property. Should such events occur, our
	operations may be adversely affected. If a property is mortgaged to secure
	payment of indebtedness and income from such property is insufficient to pay
	that indebtedness, the property could be foreclosed upon by the mortgagee
	resulting in a loss of income and a decline in our total asset value.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.25IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<B>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	We have outstanding debt, and the amount of debt
	and its cost may increase and refinancing may not be available on acceptable
	terms.
</FONT>
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	As of December 31, 2016, total debt outstanding
	was $1,056,147,000 and our ratio of total debt to total enterprise value was 35.8%.&#160;
	&#8220;Enterprise value&#8221; means the market equity value of our common stock, plus
	debt, less cash and cash equivalents at such date.&#160; In addition, we have
	significant debt service obligations.&#160; For the year ended December 31, 2016,
	our scheduled cash payments for principal and interest were $22,957,000.&#160; In
	the future, we may incur additional debt, and thus increase the ratio of total
	debt to total enterprise value.&#160; If our level of indebtedness increases, there
	may be an increased risk of default which could adversely affect our financial
	condition and results of operations.&#160; In addition, in a rising interest rate
	environment, the cost of refinancing our existing debt and any new debt or
	market rate security or instrument may increase.&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT COLOR=BLACK FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Continued
	uncertainty in the equity and credit markets may negatively impact our ability
	to obtain financing on reasonable terms or at all, which may negatively affect
	our ability to refinance our debt
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	.&#160; &nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:0IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.25IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<B>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	We might fail to qualify or remain qualified as a
	REIT, and may be required to pay income taxes at corporate rates.
</FONT>
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Although we believe that we will remain organized
	and will continue to operate so as to qualify as a REIT for federal income tax
	purposes, we might fail to remain qualified.&#160; Qualification as a REIT for
	federal income tax purposes is governed by highly technical and complex
	provisions of the Internal Revenue Code (the &#8220;Code&#8221;) for which there are only
	limited judicial or administrative interpretations and depends on various facts
	and circumstances that are not entirely within our control.&#160; In addition,
	legislation, new regulations, administrative interpretations or court decisions
	may significantly change the relevant tax laws and/or the federal income tax
	consequences of qualifying as a REIT.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	If, with respect to any taxable year, we fail to
	maintain our qualification as a REIT and do not qualify under statutory relief
	provisions, we could not deduct distributions to stockholders in computing our
	taxable income and would have to pay federal income tax on our taxable income
	at regular corporate rates. The federal income tax payable would include any
	applicable alternative minimum tax. If we had to pay federal income tax, the
	amount of money available to distribute to stockholders and pay our
	indebtedness would be reduced for the year or years involved, and we would no
	longer be required to make distributions to stockholders. In addition, we would
	also be disqualified from treatment as a REIT for the four taxable years
	following the year during which qualification was lost, unless we were entitled
	to relief under the relevant statutory provisions.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.25IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<B>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	We face possible adverse changes in tax laws,
	which may result in an increase in our tax liability.
</FONT>
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	From time to time changes in state and local tax
	laws or regulations are enacted, which may result in an increase in our tax
	liability.&#160; The shortfall in tax revenues for states and municipalities in
	recent years may lead to an increase in the frequency and size of such
	changes.&#160; If such changes occur, we may be required to pay additional taxes on
	our assets or income.&#160; These increased tax costs could adversely affect our
	financial condition and results of operations and the amount of cash available
	for payment of dividends.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:0IN;">
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</I>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.25IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<B>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	Loss of our key personnel could harm our
	operations and adversely affect the value of our common stock.
</FONT>
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	We are dependent on the efforts of Steven Roth,
	our Chief Executive Officer.&#160; Although we believe that we could find a
	replacement, the loss of his services could harm our operations and adversely
	affect the value of our common stock.
</FONT>
</P>

<HR NOSHADE STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: ALWAYS" ALIGN="CENTER" WIDTH="100%" SIZE=2>
<A NAME="eolPage14"></A>
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_PAGE_14">
</A>
<DIV BCLPAGEBORDER STYLE="PADDING-TOP: 0IN; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0IN; WIDTH: 100%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0IN; PADDING-LEFT: 0IN">
<DIV BCLHEADER>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MSO-LINE-HEIGHT-RULE:EXACTLY;MSO-PAGINATION:WIDOW-ORPHAN NO-LINE-NUMBERS;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:.7PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	ALEXANDER&#8217;S CHARTER
	DOCUMENTS AND APPLICABLE LAW MAY HINDER ANY ATTEMPT TO ACQUIRE US.
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Provisions in Alexander&#8217;s certificate of
	incorporation and by laws, as well as provisions of the Code and Delaware
	corporate law, may delay or prevent a change in control of the Company or a
	tender offer, even if such action might be beneficial to stockholders, and
	limit the stockholders&#8217; opportunity to receive a potential premium for their
	shares of common stock over then prevailing market prices.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Primarily to facilitate maintenance of its
	qualification as a REIT, Alexander&#8217;s certificate of incorporation generally
	prohibits ownership, directly, indirectly or beneficially, by any single
	stockholder of more than 9.9% of the outstanding shares of preferred stock of
	any class or 4.9% of outstanding common stock of any class.&#160; The Board of
	Directors may waive or modify these ownership limits with respect to one or
	more persons if it is satisfied that ownership in excess of these limits will
	not jeopardize Alexander&#8217;s status as a REIT for federal income tax purposes.&#160;
	In addition, the Board of Directors has, subject to certain conditions and
	limitations, exempted Vornado and certain of its affiliates from these
	ownership limitations.&#160; Stock owned in violation of these ownership limits will
	be subject to the loss of rights and other restrictions.&#160; These ownership limits
	may have the effect of inhibiting or impeding a change in control.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Alexander&#8217;s Board of Directors is divided into
	three classes of directors.&#160; Directors of each class are chosen for three-year
	staggered terms.&#160; Staggered terms of directors may have the effect of delaying
	or preventing changes in control or management, even though changes in
	management or a change in control might be in the best interest of our
	stockholders.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	In addition, Alexander&#8217;s charter documents
	authorize the Board of Directors to:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0IN;MARGIN-LEFT:.5IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE=SYMBOL LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#183;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	cause
	Alexander&#8217;s to issue additional authorized but unissued common stock or
	preferred stock;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0IN;MARGIN-LEFT:.5IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE=SYMBOL LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#183;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	classify
	or reclassify, in one or more series, any unissued preferred stock;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0IN;MARGIN-LEFT:.5IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE=SYMBOL LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#183;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	set
	the preferences, rights and other terms of any classified or reclassified stock
	that Alexander&#8217;s issues; and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0IN;MARGIN-LEFT:.5IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE=SYMBOL LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#183;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	increase,
	without stockholder approval, the number of shares of beneficial interest that
	Alexander&#8217;s may issue.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:15.1PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	The Board of Directors could establish a series of
	preferred stock with terms that could delay, deter or prevent a change in
	control of Alexander&#8217;s or other transaction that might involve a premium price
	or otherwise be in the best interest of our stockholders, although the Board of
	Directors does not, at present, intend to establish a series of preferred stock
	of this kind.&#160; Alexander&#8217;s charter documents contain other provisions that may
	delay, deter or prevent a change in control of the Company or other transaction
	that might involve a premium price or otherwise be in the best interest of our
	stockholders.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	In addition, Vornado, Interstate and its three
	general partners (each of whom are both trustees of Vornado and Directors of
	Alexander&#8217;s) together beneficially own approximately 58.7% of our outstanding shares
	of common stock.&#160; This degree of ownership is likely to reduce the possibility
	of a tender offer or an attempt to change control of the Company by a third
	party.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:0IN;">
<B>
<I>
<FONT COLOR=BLACK FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.25IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<B>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	We may change our policies without obtaining the
	approval of our stockholders.
</FONT>
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Our operating and financial policies, including our
	policies with respect to acquisitions of real estate or other assets, growth,
	operations, indebtedness, capitalization and dividends, are exclusively
	determined by our Board of Directors.&#160; Accordingly, our stockholders do not
	control these policies.
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:0IN;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	OUR OWNERSHIP STRUCTURE AND RELATED-PARTY
	TRANSACTIONS MAY GIVE RISE TO CONFLICTS OF INTEREST.
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.25IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<B>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	Steven Roth, Vornado and Interstate may exercise
	substantial influence over us.&#160; They and some of our other directors and
	officers have interests or positions in other entities that may compete with
	us.
</FONT>
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	As of December 31, 2016, Interstate and its
	partners owned approximately 7.1% of the common shares of beneficial interest
	of Vornado and approximately 26.3% of our outstanding common stock.&#160; Steven Roth, David Mandelbaum and Russell B. Wight, Jr. are the partners of Interstate.&#160;
	Mr.&nbsp;Roth is the Chairman of our Board of Directors and Chief Executive
	Officer, the Chairman of the Board of Trustees and Chief Executive Officer of
	Vornado and the Managing General Partner of Interstate.&#160; Mr.&nbsp;Wight and
	Mr.&nbsp;Mandelbaum are both trustees of Vornado and members of our Board of
	Directors.&#160; In addition, Vornado manages and leases the real estate assets of
	Interstate.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	As of December 31, 2016, Vornado owned 32.4% of
	our outstanding common stock, in addition to the 26.3% owned by Interstate and
	its partners.&#160; In addition to the relationships described in the immediately
	preceding paragraph, Dr. Richard West is a trustee of Vornado and a member of
	our Board of Directors and Joseph Macnow is our Executive Vice President and
	Chief Financial Officer and the Executive Vice President &#8211; Finance and Chief
	Administrative Officer of Vornado.&#160; Stephen W. Theriot, our Assistant
	Treasurer, is the Chief Financial Officer of Vornado.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Because of their overlapping interests, Vornado,
	Mr.&nbsp;Roth, Interstate and the other individuals noted in the preceding
	paragraphs may have substantial influence over Alexander&#8217;s, and on the outcome
	of any matters submitted to Alexander&#8217;s stockholders for approval.&#160; In
	addition, certain decisions concerning our operations or financial structure
	may present conflicts of interest among Vornado, Messrs.&nbsp;Roth, Mandelbaum
	and Wight and Interstate and other security holders.&#160; Vornado, Mr.&nbsp;Roth
	and Interstate may, in the future, engage in a wide variety of activities in
	the real estate business which may result in conflicts of interest with respect
	to matters affecting us, such as, which of these entities or persons, if any,
	may take advantage of potential business opportunities, the business focus of
	these entities, the types of properties and geographic locations in which these
	entities make investments, potential competition between business activities
	conducted, or sought to be conducted, by us, competition for properties and
	tenants, possible corporate transactions such as acquisitions, and other
	strategic decisions affecting the future of these entities.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.25IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<B>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	There may be conflicts of interest between
	Vornado, its affiliates and us.
</FONT>
</I>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Vornado manages, develops and leases our properties
	under agreements that have one-year terms expiring in March of each year, which
	are automatically renewable.&#160; Because we share common senior management with
	Vornado and because four of the trustees of Vornado are on our Board of
	Directors, the terms of the foregoing agreements and any future agreements may
	not be comparable to those we could have negotiated with an unaffiliated third
	party.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	For a description of Interstate&#8217;s ownership of
	Vornado and Alexander&#8217;s, see &#8220;Steven Roth, Vornado and Interstate may exercise
	substantial influence over us.&#160; They and some of our other directors and
	officers have interests or positions in other entities that may compete with
	us.&#8221; above.
</FONT>

	volatile and may continue to fluctuate widely as a result of a number of
	factors, many of which are outside of our control.&#160; In addition, the stock
	market is subject to fluctuations in the share prices and trading volumes that
	affect the market prices of the shares of many companies.&#160; These broad market
	fluctuations have in the past and may in the future adversely affect the market
	price of our common shares.&#160; Among the factors that could affect the price of
	our common shares are:

</FONT>
</I>
</B>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	The interest of our current stockholders could be
	diluted if we issue additional equity securities.&#160; As of December 31, 2016, we
	had authorized but unissued 4,826,550 shares of common stock, par value of
	$1.00 per share and 3,000,000 shares of preferred stock, par value $1.00 per
	share; of which 8,505 shares of common stock are reserved for issuance upon
	redemption of the deferred stock units previously granted to our Board of
	Directors.&#160; In addition, 498,376 shares are available for future grant under
	the terms of our 2016 Omnibus Stock Plan.&#160; These awards may be granted in the
	form of options, restricted stock, stock appreciation rights, deferred stock
	units, or other equity-based interests, and if granted, would reduce that
	number of shares available for future grants, provided however that an award
	that may be settled only in cash, would not reduce the number of shares
	available under the plan.&#160; We cannot predict the impact that future issuances
	of common or preferred stock or any exercise of outstanding options or grants
	of additional equity-based interests would have on the market price of our
	common stock.
</FONT>

<DIV BCLHEADER>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MSO-LINE-HEIGHT-RULE:EXACTLY;MSO-PAGINATION:WIDOW-ORPHAN NO-LINE-NUMBERS;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:.7PT;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.75IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.75IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;">
	ITEM 2.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; PROPERTIES &#8211;
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN BOLD,SERIF" STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN BOLD,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:NONE;">
	continued
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<H1 STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;LINE-HEIGHT:12.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</H1>
<H1 STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;LINE-HEIGHT:12.0PT;">
	Operating
	Properties
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</H1>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:10.0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT FACE=CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE=CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<H5 STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:13.7PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;LETTER-SPACING:0PT;">
	731 Lexington Avenue
</FONT>
</U>
</I>
</FONT>
</H5>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	731 Lexington Avenue, a 1,311,000 square foot multi-use building,
	comprises the entire block bounded by Lexington Avenue, East 59
<SUP>
	th
</SUP>
	Street, Third Avenue and East 58
<SUP>
	th
</SUP>
	Street in Manhattan, New York,
	and is situated in the heart of one of Manhattan&#8217;s busiest business and
	shopping districts, with convenient access to several subway and bus lines. The
	property is located across the street from Bloomingdale&#8217;s flagship store and
	only a few blocks away from Fifth Avenue and 57
<SUP>
	th
</SUP>
	Street.&#160; The
	building contains 889,000 and 174,000 of net rentable square feet of office and
	retail space, respectively, which we own, and 248,000 square feet of
	residential space consisting of 105 condominium units, which we sold.&#160;
	Bloomberg occupies all of the office space.&#160; The Home Depot (83,000 square
	feet), The Container Store (34,000 square feet) and Hennes &amp; Mauritz
	(27,000 square feet) are the principal retail tenants.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	In January 2016, we entered into a lease amendment with
	Bloomberg which extends the lease term related to 192,000 square feet of office
	space at our 731 Lexington Avenue property to be coterminous with the other
	697,000 square feet of office space leased by Bloomberg through February 2029,
	with a ten-year extension option.&#160; In connection with the lease amendment, Bloomberg
	provided a $200,000,000 letter of credit, which amount may be reduced in
	certain circumstances. We may draw on this letter of credit subject to certain
	terms of the lease amendment, including an event of default by Bloomberg.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	The office portion of 731 Lexington Avenue is encumbered by
	a mortgage loan with a balance of $300,000,000 as of December 31, 2016.&#160; The
	interest-only loan is at LIBOR plus 0.95% (1.65% as of December 31, 2016) and
	matures in March 2017, with four one-year extension options. In connection
	therewith, we purchased an interest rate cap with a notional amount of $300,000,000
	that caps LIBOR at a rate of 6.0%.&#160;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	The retail portion of 731 Lexington Avenue is encumbered by
	a mortgage loan with a balance of $350,000,000 as of December 31, 2016. The
	interest-only loan is at LIBOR plus 1.40% (2.05% as of December 31, 2016) and
	matures in August 2020, with two one-year extension options.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:0IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<H5 STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:13.7PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;">
	Rego
	Park I
</FONT>
</U>
</I>
</FONT>
</H5>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Rego Park I, a 343,000 square foot shopping center, located
	on Queens Boulevard and 63
<SUP>
	rd
</SUP>
	Road in Queens, New York, is anchored
	by a 195,000 square foot Sears department store, a 50,000 square foot
	Burlington Coat Factory, a 46,000 square foot Bed Bath &amp; Beyond and a
	36,000 square foot Marshalls. In January 2017, Sears announced that it plans to
	close its store in the second quarter of 2017. Under the terms of the lease,
	Sears is obligated to pay rent through lease expiration in March of 2021. The
	center contains a parking deck (1,241 spaces) that provides for paid parking.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	In March 2016, we completed a two-year extension of the 100%
	cash collateralized loan with a balance of $78,246,000 as of December 31,
	2016.&#160; The loan bears interest at 0.35%, is prepayable at any time without
	penalty and matures in March 2018.&#160;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<H5 STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:13.7PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;">
	Rego
	Park II
</FONT>
</U>
</I>
</FONT>
</H5>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Rego Park II, a 609,000 square foot shopping center,
	adjacent to the Rego Park I shopping center in Queens, New York, is anchored by
	a 145,000 square foot Costco, a 135,000 square foot Century 21 and a 133,000
	square foot Kohl&#8217;s.&#160; In addition, 47,000 square feet is leased to Toys &#8220;R&#8221;
	Us/Babies &#8220;R&#8221; Us, a one-third owned affiliate of Vornado.&#160; The center contains
	a parking deck (1,326 spaces) that provides for paid parking.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	This center is encumbered by a first mortgage loan with a
	balance of $259,901,000 as of December 31, 2016.&#160; The loan bears interest at LIBOR
	plus 1.85% (2.62% as of December 31, 2016) and matures in November 2018.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<H5 STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:13.7PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;">
	The
	Alexander Apartment Tower
</FONT>
</U>
</I>
</FONT>
</H5>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	The Alexander apartment tower, located above our Rego Park
	II shopping center, contains 312 units aggregating 255,000 square feet and is
	98.1% leased as of December 31, 2016.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<H5 STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:13.7PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</I>
</FONT>
</H5>
<H5 STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:13.7PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;">
	Paramus
</FONT>
</U>
</I>
</FONT>
</H5>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	We own 30.3 acres of land located at the intersection of
	Routes 4 and 17 in Paramus, New Jersey.&#160; The land is located directly across
	from the Garden State Plaza regional shopping mall and is within two miles of
	three other regional shopping malls and ten miles of New York City.&#160; The land
	has been ground leased to IKEA Property, Inc. since 2001.&#160; The lease expires in
	2041, with a purchase option in 2021 for $75,000,000.&#160; The property is
	encumbered by a $68,000,000 interest-only mortgage loan with a fixed rate of
	2.90%, which matures in October 2018.&#160; The annual triple-net rent is the sum of
	$700,000 plus the amount of debt service on the mortgage loan.&#160; If the purchase
	option is exercised, we will receive net cash proceeds of approximately
	$7,000,000 and recognize a gain on sale of land of approximately $60,000,000.&#160;
	If the purchase option is not exercised, the triple-net rent for the last 20
	years would include debt service sufficient to fully amortize $68,000,000 over
	the remaining 20-year lease term.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<H5 STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:13.7PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	&nbsp;

</I>

</H5>
<H5 STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:13.7PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;">
	Flushing
</FONT>
</U>
</I>
</FONT>
</H5>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Flushing is located on Roosevelt Avenue and Main Street in
	the downtown, commercial section of Flushing, Queens, New York.&#160; Roosevelt Avenue and Main Street are active shopping districts and there are many national
	retailers located in the area.&#160; A subway entrance is located directly in front
	of the property with bus service across the street.&#160; The property comprises a
	four-floor building containing 167,000 square feet and a parking garage, which
	is sub-leased to New World Mall LLC for the remainder of our ground lease term,
	which expires in 2027 and has one 10-year extension option.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>

<EFX_LEGAL_PROCEEDINGS>
<A NAME="FIS_LEGAL_PROCEEDINGS"></A>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;">
	ITEM 3.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; LEGAL PROCEEDINGS
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	We are from time to time involved in legal actions arising
	in the ordinary course of business.&#160; In our opinion, after consultation with
	our legal counsel, the outcome of such matters will not have a material effect
	on our financial condition, results of operations or cash flows.&#160;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:1.0PT;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:16.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	On June 24, 2014,
	Sears Roebuck and Co. (&#8220;Sears&#8221;) filed a lawsuit in the Supreme Court of the
	State of New York against Vornado and us (and certain of our subsidiaries) with
	regard to space that Sears leases at our Rego Park I property alleging that the
	defendants are liable for harm Sears has suffered as a result of (a) water
	intrusions into the premises, (b) two fires in February 2014 that caused
	damages to those premises, and (c) alleged violations of the Americans with
	Disabilities Act in the premises&#8217; parking garage.&nbsp; Sears asserted various
	causes of actions for damages and sought to compel compliance with landlord&#8217;s
	obligations to repair the premises and to provide security, and to compel us to
	abate a nuisance that Sears claims was a cause of the water intrusions into its
	premises.&nbsp; In addition to injunctive relief, Sears sought, among other
	things, damages of not less than $4 million and future damages it estimated
	would not be less than $25 million.&nbsp;In March 2016, Sears withdrew its
	claim for future damages leaving a remaining claim for property damages, which
	we estimate to be approximately $650,000 based on information provided by
	Sears. We intend to defend the remaining claim vigorously. The amount or range
	of reasonable possible losses, if any, is not expected to be greater than
	$650,000.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
</EFX_LEGAL_PROCEEDINGS>

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.5IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	The following graph is a
	comparison of the five-year cumulative return of our common stock, the Standard
	&amp; Poor&#8217;s 500 Index (the &#8220;S&amp;P 500 Index&#8221;) and the National Association
	of Real Estate Investment Trusts&#8217; (&#8220;NAREIT&#8221;) All Equity Index, a peer group
	index.&#160; The graph assumes that $100 was invested on December 31, 2011 in our
	common stock, the S&amp;P 500 Index and the NAREIT All Equity Index and that
	all dividends were reinvested without the payment of any commissions.&#160; There
	can be no assurance that the performance of our stock will continue in line
	with the same or similar trends depicted in the graph below.
</FONT>
</P>

<DIV BCLHEADER>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MSO-LINE-HEIGHT-RULE:EXACTLY;MSO-PAGINATION:WIDOW-ORPHAN NO-LINE-NUMBERS;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:.7PT;">
	&nbsp;

</DIV>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.75IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.75IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;">
	ITEM 7.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; management&#8217;s
	discussion and analysis of financial condition and results of operations
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<H4 STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;">
	Overview
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</H4>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Alexander&#8217;s,
	Inc. (NYSE: ALX) is a real estate investment trust (&#8220;REIT&#8221;), incorporated in
	Delaware, engaged in leasing, managing, developing and redeveloping its
	properties.&#160; All references to &#8220;we,&#8221; &#8220;us,&#8221; &#8220;our,&#8221; &#8220;Company,&#8221; and &#8220;Alexander&#8217;s&#8221;,
	refer to Alexander&#8217;s, Inc. and its consolidated subsidiaries.&#160; We are managed
	by, and our properties are leased and developed by, Vornado Realty Trust
	(&#8220;Vornado&#8221;) (NYSE: VNO).&#160; We have seven properties in the greater New York City
	metropolitan area.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	We
	compete with a large number of property owners and developers.&#160; Our success
	depends upon, among other factors, trends of the global, national and local
	economies, the financial condition and operating results of current and
	prospective tenants and customers, the availability and cost of capital,
	construction and renovation costs, taxes, governmental regulations,
	legislation, population and employment trends, zoning laws, and our ability to
	lease, sublease or sell our properties, at profitable levels.&#160; Our success is
	also subject to our ability to refinance existing debt on acceptable terms as
	it comes due.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:0IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Year Ended December 31, 2016
	Financial Results Summary
</FONT>
</U>
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Net
	income for the year ended December 31, 2016 was $86,477,000, or $16.91 per
	diluted share, compared to $76,907,000, or $15.04 per diluted share for the
	year ended December 31, 2015.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Funds
	from operations (&#8220;FFO&#8221;) for the year ended December 31, 2016 was $119,780,000,
	or $23.42 per diluted share, compared to $107,648,000, or $21.06 per diluted
	share for the year ended December 31, 2015.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:0IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Quarter Ended December 31, 2016
	Financial Results Summary
</FONT>
</U>
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Net
	income for the quarter ended December 31, 2016 was $21,655,000, or $4.23 per
	diluted share, compared to $23,572,000, or $4.61 per diluted share for the
	quarter ended December 31, 2015.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	FFO
	for the quarter ended December 31, 2016 was $29,582,000, or $5.78 per diluted share,
	compared to $31,730,000, or $6.21 per diluted share for the quarter ended
	December 31, 2015.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Net income and FFO for the quarter
	ended December 31, 2015 included $3,911,000, or $0.77 per diluted share from a
	special dividend from an investment in marketable securities and higher income
	from bankruptcy recoveries
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#160;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<DIV BCLFOOTER>

</DIV>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Overview &#8211; continued
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Square
	Footage, Occupancy and Leasing Activity
</FONT>
</U>
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	As of December 31, 2016 our portfolio was comprised of
	seven properties aggregating 2,437,000 square feet.&#160; As of December 31, 2016,
	our properties had an occupancy rate of 99.8%.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<H4 STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;">
	Significant Tenants
</FONT>
</U>
</I>
</FONT>
</H4>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Bloomberg
	accounted for $104,590,000, $94,468,000 and $91,109,000, representing
	approximately 46%, 45% and 45% of our total revenues in each of the years ended
	December 31, 2016, 2015 and 2014, respectively.&#160; No other tenant accounted for
	more than 10% of our total revenues.&#160; If we were to lose Bloomberg as a tenant,
	or if Bloomberg were to be unable to fulfill its obligations under its lease,
	it would adversely affect our results of operations and financial condition.&#160;
	In order to assist us in our continuing assessment of Bloomberg&#8217;s
	creditworthiness, we receive certain confidential financial information and
	metrics from Bloomberg.&#160; In addition, we access and evaluate financial
	information regarding Bloomberg from other private sources, as well as publicly
	available data.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	In
	January 2016, we entered into a lease amendment with Bloomberg which extends
	the lease term related to 192,000 square feet of office space at our 731
	Lexington Avenue property to be coterminous with the other 697,000 square feet
	of office space leased by Bloomberg through February 2029, with a ten-year
	extension option.&#160; In connection with the lease amendment, Bloomberg provided a
	$200,000,000 letter of credit, which amount may be reduced in certain
	circumstances. We may draw on this letter of credit subject to certain terms of
	the lease amendment, including an event of default by Bloomberg.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<H4 STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;">
	Financing
</FONT>
</U>
</I>
</FONT>
</H4>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	In March 2016 we completed a two-year extension of the 100%
	cash collateralized loan with a balance of $78,246,000 as of December 31, 2016.
	The loan bears interest at 0.35%, is prepayable at any time without penalty and
	matures in March 2018.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#160;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<H4 STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;">
	Critical Accounting Policies and Estimates
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</H4>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#160;Our
	financial statements are prepared in conformity with accounting principles
	generally accepted in the United States of America (&#8220;GAAP&#8221;), which requires us
	to make estimates and assumptions that affect the reported amounts of assets
	and liabilities and disclosure of contingent assets and liabilities at the date
	of the financial statements and the reported amounts of revenues and expenses
	during the reporting periods.&#160; Actual results could differ from those
	estimates.&#160; Set forth below is a summary of our accounting policies that we
	believe are critical to the preparation of our consolidated financial
	statements.&#160; This summary should be read in conjunction with a more complete
	discussion of our accounting policies included in Note 2 &#8211;
</FONT>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Summary of
	Significant
</FONT>
</I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
</FONT>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Accounting Policies,
</FONT>
</I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	to the consolidated financial
	statements in this Annual Report on Form 10-K.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.3IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Real Estate
</FONT>
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.3IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Real
	estate is carried at cost, net of accumulated depreciation and amortization.&#160;
	As of December 31, 2016 and 2015, the carrying amount of our real estate, net
	of accumulated depreciation and amortization, was $780,814,000 and $803,939,000,
	respectively.&#160; Maintenance and repairs are expensed as incurred.&#160; Depreciation
	requires an estimate by management of the useful life of each property and
	improvement as well as an allocation of the costs associated with a property to
	its various components. If we do not allocate these costs appropriately or incorrectly
	estimate the useful lives of our real estate, depreciation expense may be
	misstated. We capitalize all property operating expenses directly associated
	with and attributable to, the development and construction of a project,
	including interest expense. The capitalization period begins when development
	activities are underway and ends when it is determined that the asset is
	substantially complete and ready for its intended use, which is typically
	evidenced by the receipt of a temporary certificate of occupancy. General and
	administrative costs are expensed as incurred.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
<H4 STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
	&nbsp;
</H4>
<DIV BCLFOOTER>
<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MSO-BORDER-SHADOW:YES;MSO-PADDING-ALT:31.0PT 31.0PT 31.0PT 31.0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MSO-FAREAST-FONT-FAMILY:TIMES NEW ROMAN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

<HR NOSHADE STYLE="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: ALWAYS" ALIGN="CENTER" WIDTH="100%" SIZE=2>
<A NAME="eolPage25"></A>
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_PAGE_25">
</A>
<DIV BCLPAGEBORDER STYLE="PADDING-TOP: 0IN; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0IN; WIDTH: 100%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0IN; PADDING-LEFT: 0IN">
<DIV BCLHEADER>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MSO-LINE-HEIGHT-RULE:EXACTLY;MSO-PAGINATION:WIDOW-ORPHAN NO-LINE-NUMBERS;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:.7PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<H4 STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;">
	Critical Accounting Policies
	and Estimates &#8211; continued
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</H4>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Our
	properties and related intangible assets, including properties to be developed
	in the future and currently under development, are individually reviewed for
	impairment whenever events or changes in circumstances indicate that the
	carrying amount of the assets may not be recoverable.&#160; An impairment exists
	when the carrying amount of an asset exceeds the sum of the undiscounted cash
	flows expected to result from the use and eventual disposition of the asset.&#160;
	Estimates of future cash flows are based on our current plans, intended holding
	periods and available market information at the time the analyses are
	prepared.&#160; For our development properties, estimates of future cash flows also
	include all future expenditures necessary to develop the asset, including
	interest payments that will be capitalized as part of the cost of the asset.&#160;
	An impairment loss is recognized only if the carrying amount of the asset is not
	recoverable and is measured based on the excess of the property&#8217;s carrying
	amount over its estimated fair value.&#160; If our estimates of future cash flows,
	anticipated holding periods, or fair values change, based on market conditions
	or otherwise, our evaluation of impairment charges may be different and such
	differences could be material to our consolidated financial statements.&#160;
	Estimates of future cash flows are subjective and are based, in part, on
	assumptions regarding future occupancy, rental rates and capital requirements
	that could differ materially from actual results.&#160; Plans to hold properties
	over longer periods decrease the likelihood of recording impairment losses.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.3IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.3IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Allowance for Doubtful Accounts
</FONT>
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:0IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:8.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	We
	periodically evaluate the collectibility of amounts due from tenants, including
	the receivable arising from the straight-lining of rents, and maintain an
	allowance for doubtful accounts ($1,473,000 and $918,000 as of December 31,
	2016 and 2015, respectively) for estimated losses resulting from the inability
	of tenants to make required payments under the lease agreements.&#160; We exercise
	judgment in establishing these allowances and consider payment history and
	current credit status in developing these estimates.&#160; These estimates may
	differ from actual results, which could be material to our consolidated
	financial statements.&#160;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.25IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	Revenue Recognition
</FONT>
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	We have the following revenue sources
	and revenue recognition policies:
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.3IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.45IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE=SYMBOL STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE=SYMBOL LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#183;
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT FACE=SYMBOL STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE=SYMBOL LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; &nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Base
	Rent &#8211; revenue arising from tenant leases.&#160; These rents are recognized over the
	non-cancelable term of the related leases on a straight-line basis, which
	includes the effects of rent steps and free rent abatements under the leases.&#160;
	We commence rental revenue recognition when the tenant takes possession of the
	leased space and the leased space is substantially ready for its intended use.&#160;
	In addition, in circumstances where we provide a tenant improvement allowance
	for improvements that are owned by the tenant, we recognize the allowance as a
	reduction of rental revenue on a straight-line basis over the term of the
	lease.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.3IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.45IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE=SYMBOL STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE=SYMBOL LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#183;
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT FACE=SYMBOL STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE=SYMBOL LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; &nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Percentage
	Rent &#8211; revenue arising from retail tenant leases that is contingent upon the
	sales of tenants exceeding defined thresholds.&#160; These rents are recognized only
	after the contingency has been removed (i.e., when tenant sales thresholds have
	been achieved).
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.3IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.45IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE=SYMBOL STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE=SYMBOL LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#183;
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT FACE=SYMBOL STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE=SYMBOL LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; &nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Expense
	Reimbursements &#8211; revenue arising from tenant leases which provide for the recovery
	of all or a portion of the operating expenses and real estate taxes of the
	respective properties.&#160; This revenue is recognized in the same periods as the
	expenses are incurred.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.3IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.45IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE=SYMBOL STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE=SYMBOL LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#183;
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT FACE=SYMBOL STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE=SYMBOL LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; &nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Parking
	income &#8211; revenue arising from the rental of parking space at our properties.&#160;
	This income is recognized as the service is provided.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.45IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Before
	we recognize revenue, we assess, among other things, its collectibility.&#160; If
	our assessment of the collectibility of revenue changes, the impact on our
	consolidated financial statements could be material.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.3IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.25IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	Income Taxes
</FONT>
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	We
	operate in a manner intended to enable us to continue to qualify as a REIT
	under Sections 856 &#8211; 860 of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended (the
	&#8220;Code&#8221;).&#160; In order to maintain our qualification as a REIT under the Code, we
	must distribute at least 90% of our taxable income to stockholders each year.&#160;
	We distribute to our stockholders 100% of our taxable income and therefore, no
	provision for Federal income taxes is required.&#160; If we fail to distribute the
	required amount of income to our stockholders, or fail to meet other REIT
	requirements, we may fail to qualify as a REIT, which may result in substantial
	adverse tax consequences.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<H1 ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:LEFT;">
	&nbsp;
</H1>

	Ended

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;LINE-HEIGHT:12.0PT;">
	December 31, 2016 compared to December
	31, 2015
</FONT>
</B>

</H1>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:7.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;">
	Property Rentals
</FONT>
</U>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:20.15PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Property rentals were $151,444,000 in the year ended December
	31, 2016, compared to $138,688,000 in the prior year, an increase of $12,756,000.&#160;
	This increase was primarily due to (i) rental income of $7,271,000 from The
	Alexander apartment tower, which was placed in service in phases beginning July
	2015, (ii) higher rental income of $3,366,000 from the January 2016 lease
	amendment with Bloomberg at 731 Lexington Avenue and (iii) income of $2,257,000
	resulting from a tenant lease termination at our Rego Park II property.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:20.15PT;">

</FONT>
</U>
</FONT>

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:20.15PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Tenant expense reimbursements were $75,492,000 in the year
	ended December 31, 2016, compared to $69,227,000 in the prior year, an increase
	of $6,265,000. This increase was primarily due to (i) higher recoveries of real
	estate taxes and operating expenses from Bloomberg at 731 Lexington Avenue as a
	result of the January 2016 lease amendment, which converted 192,000 square feet
	from a gross basis to a net rent basis and (ii) higher reimbursable real estate
	taxes, partially offset by (iii) lower reimbursable operating expenses.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:20.15PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Operating expenses were $82,232,000 in the year ended
	December 31, 2016, compared to $76,218,000 in the prior year, an increase of
	$6,014,000.&#160; This increase was primarily due to (i) higher operating expenses
	of $2,494,000 related to The Alexander apartment tower, which was placed in
	service in phases beginning July 2015, (ii) higher reimbursable real estate
	taxes of $3,703,000 and (iii) higher bad debt expense of $871,000, partially
	offset by (iv) lower reimbursable operating expenses of $1,068,000.
</FONT>
</FONT>

	Interest and other income, net was $3,305,000 in the year
	ended December 31, 2016, compared to $5,949,000 in the prior year, a decrease
	of $2,644,000.&#160; This decrease was primarily due to $2,141,000 from a special
	dividend from our investment in common shares of Macerich in 2015 and lower
	income of $1,275,000 in connection with bankruptcy recoveries.

	Expense
</FONT>

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:20.15PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Interest
	and debt expense was $22,241,000 in the year ended December 31, 2016, compared
	to $24,239,000 in the prior year, a decrease of $1,998,000.&#160; This decrease was
	primarily due to savings of $5,631,000 resulting from the refinancing of the
	retail portion of 731 Lexington Avenue on August 5, 2015 at LIBOR plus 1.40%,
	or 2.05% as of December 31, 2016 (the prior loan had a fixed rate of 4.93%);
	partially offset by lower capitalized interest of $1,486,000 as a result of
	completing the development of The Alexander apartment tower and higher average LIBOR
	of $2,066,000.
</FONT>
</FONT>
