<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	ALEXANDER&#8217;S, INC. AND SUBSIDIARIES
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED
	FINANCIAL STATEMENTS (CONTINUED)
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	2.&#160;&#160;&#160; SUMMARY OF SIGNIFICANT ACCOUNTING POLICIES - continued
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_3AD6A1FB2ABC40928DDDA7AFA">
</A>
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_0480BEDB915245A5A0618D94D">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Revenue
	Recognition
</FONT>
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#8211; We have the following
	revenue sources and revenue recognition policies:
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:7.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Base
	Rent
</FONT>
</U>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#8211; revenue arising from tenant leases.
	&#160;These rents are recognized over the non-cancelable term of the related leases
	on a straight-line basis, which includes the effects of rent steps and free
	rent abatements under the leases.&#160; We commence rental revenue recognition when
	the tenant takes possession of the leased space and the leased space is
	substantially ready for its intended use.&#160; In addition, in circumstances where
	we provide a tenant improvement allowance for improvements that are owned by
	the tenant, we recognize the allowance as a reduction of rental revenue on a
	straight-line basis over the term of the lease.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:7.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Percentage
	Rent
</FONT>
</U>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#8211; revenue arising from retail tenant
	leases that is contingent upon the sales of tenants exceeding defined thresholds.
	&#160;These rents are recognized only after the contingency has been removed (i.e., when
	tenant sales thresholds have been achieved).
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:7.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Expense
	Reimbursements
</FONT>
</U>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#8211; revenue arising from
	tenant leases which provide for the recovery of all or a portion of the
	operating expenses and real estate taxes of the respective properties. &#160;This
	revenue is recognized in the same periods as the expenses are incurred.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:7.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Parking
	Income
</FONT>
</U>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#8211; revenue arising from the rental
	of parking space at our properties.&#160; This income is recognized as the service
	is provided.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:0IN;">
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_0480BEDB915245A5A0618D94D_BCLEND">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_9345C4A189C1413A88AC4225F">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Income
	Taxes
</FONT>
</I>
</B>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#8211; We operate in a manner
	intended to enable us to continue to qualify as a REIT under Sections 856 &#8211; 860
	of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended (the &#8220;Code&#8221;).&#160; In order to
	maintain our qualification as a REIT under the Code, we must distribute at
	least
</FONT>
</FONT>
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_8236C9F447F443E3868BE322F">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	90
</FONT>
</FONT>
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_8236C9F447F443E3868BE322F_BCLEND">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	%
	of our taxable income to stockholders each year.&#160; We distribute to our
	stockholders
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_5111CA0B8A584DF69EDA67504">
</A>
	100
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_5111CA0B8A584DF69EDA67504_BCLEND">
</A>
	% of our taxable income and
	therefore, no provision for Federal income taxes is required.&#160; Dividends
	distributed for the year ended December 31, 2016 were characterized, for
	federal income taxes, as
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_04B0734E2F824A34929841FAE">
</A>
	97.7
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_04B0734E2F824A34929841FAE_BCLEND">
</A>
	% ordinary income and
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_6E7E9BC1589542898F8A514B0">
</A>
	2.3
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_6E7E9BC1589542898F8A514B0_BCLEND">
</A>
	% long-term capital gain
	income. Dividends distributed for the year ended December 31, 2015 were
	characterized, for federal income taxes, as
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_0EFE9DDB4AB54D498AB60C355">
</A>
	97.3
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_0EFE9DDB4AB54D498AB60C355_BCLEND">
</A>
	% ordinary income and
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_7DCEE8DC2EDD4B79AE23A757C">
</A>
	2.7
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_7DCEE8DC2EDD4B79AE23A757C_BCLEND">
</A>
	% long-term capital gain
	income. Dividends distributed for the year ended December 31, 2014 were
	categorized, for federal income tax purposes, as ordinary income.&#160;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_9345C4A189C1413A88AC4225F_BCLEND">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	The
	following table reconciles our net income to estimated taxable income for the
	years ended December 31, 2016, 2015 and 2014.
</FONT>
</FONT>
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_3AD6A1FB2ABC40928DDDA7AFA_BCLEND">

	Vornado, pursuant to the agreements described below, which expire in March of
	each year and are automatically renewable.

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Steven
	Roth is the Chairman of our Board of Directors and Chief Executive Officer, the
	Managing General Partner of Interstate Properties (&#8220;Interstate&#8221;), a New Jersey
	general partnership, and the Chairman of the Board of Trustees and Chief
	Executive Officer of Vornado.&#160; As of December 31, 2016, Mr.&nbsp;Roth,
	Interstate and its other two general partners, David Mandelbaum and Russell B.
	Wight, Jr. (who are also directors of the Company and trustees of Vornado)
	owned, in the aggregate,
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_58A1391CB66A4A8FB60AC3819">
</A>
	26.3
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_58A1391CB66A4A8FB60AC3819_BCLEND">
</A>
	% of our outstanding common
	stock, in addition to the
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_D61D2E01D65A4D7081059B571">

	2.2
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_D61D2E01D65A4D7081059B571_BCLEND">
</A>
	% they indirectly own
	through Vornado.&#160; Joseph Macnow, our Executive Vice President and Chief Financial
	Officer, is the Executive Vice President &#8211; Finance and Chief Administrative
	Officer of Vornado.&#160; Stephen W. Theriot, our Assistant Treasurer, is the Chief
	Financial Officer of Vornado.
</FONT>

<I>

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">

	We
	pay Vornado an annual management fee equal to the sum of (i) $
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_B4D07C12C51A4DD392608C7B0">
</A>
	2,800,000
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_B4D07C12C51A4DD392608C7B0_BCLEND">
</A>
	, (ii)
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_7CFCC9B88CBD4EFB8BDF8B563">
</A>
	2
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_7CFCC9B88CBD4EFB8BDF8B563_BCLEND">
</A>
	% of gross revenue from the
	Rego Park II shopping center, (iii) $
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_DEBDAA5538E74C349F4AA4D80">
</A>
	0.50
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_DEBDAA5538E74C349F4AA4D80_BCLEND">
</A>
	per square foot of the
	tenant-occupied office and retail space at 731 Lexington Avenue, and (iv) $
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_A724A6095E634EEE8F7C202EF">
</A>
	297,000
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_A724A6095E634EEE8F7C202EF_BCLEND">
</A>
	, escalating at
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_40D83CFF27E74AA995277AD3E">
</A>
	3
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_40D83CFF27E74AA995277AD3E_BCLEND">
</A>
	% per annum, for managing
	the common area of 731 Lexington Avenue.&#160; Vornado is also entitled to a
	development fee equal to
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_D57BED34ACED4405BF4EE7325">
</A>
	6
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_D57BED34ACED4405BF4EE7325_BCLEND">
</A>
	% of development costs, as
	defined.

<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;">

	Agreements
</FONT>

</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>

	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Vornado
	also provides us with leasing services for a fee of
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_46E152CE7B4D4757A3B5256C7">
</A>
	3
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_46E152CE7B4D4757A3B5256C7_BCLEND">
</A>
	% of rent for the first ten
	years of a lease term,
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_EC71842FD5804842BD7F2B9EA">
</A>
	2
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_EC71842FD5804842BD7F2B9EA_BCLEND">
</A>
	% of rent for the eleventh
	through the twentieth year of a lease term, and
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_29BF4B61C3184704809C8901E">
</A>
	1
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_29BF4B61C3184704809C8901E_BCLEND">
</A>
	% of rent for the
	twenty-first through thirtieth year of a lease term, subject to the payment of
	rents by tenants.&#160; In the event third-party real estate brokers are used, the
	fees to Vornado increase by
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_33A498C6AD8A4E36B6DFF3259">
</A>
	1
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_33A498C6AD8A4E36B6DFF3259_BCLEND">
</A>
	% and Vornado is
	responsible for the fees to the third-party real estate brokers.&#160;
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_B8103EE44E1C4176830F008DD">
</A>
	Vornado is also entitled to a
	commission upon the sale of any of our assets equal to
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_7F1E5784BE644D999527A17F9">
</A>
	3
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_7F1E5784BE644D999527A17F9_BCLEND">
</A>
	% of gross proceeds, as
	defined, for asset sales less than $
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_B7CF140D6EE14D7ABC7A1EC1D">
</A>
	50,000,000
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_B7CF140D6EE14D7ABC7A1EC1D_BCLEND">
</A>
	and
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_F95613A9FB454FC491DC5BAF2">
</A>
	1
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_F95613A9FB454FC491DC5BAF2_BCLEND">
</A>
	% of gross proceeds, as
	defined, for asset sales of $50,000,000 or more.&#160; Prior to December 22, 2014,
	the total of these amounts was payable in annual installments in an amount not
	to exceed $
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_E2BC071C15EF4DFB97B014F77">
</A>
	4,000,000
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_E2BC071C15EF4DFB97B014F77_BCLEND">
</A>
	, with interest on the
	unpaid balance at
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_F04A0905B79048B988CFA3DF4">
</A>
	one-year LIBOR
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_F04A0905B79048B988CFA3DF4_BCLEND">
</A>
	plus
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_263FD1313D2F48B498E339149">
</A>
	1.0
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_263FD1313D2F48B498E339149_BCLEND">
</A>
	%
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_B8103EE44E1C4176830F008DD_BCLEND">
</A>
	.&#160; On December 22, 2014,
	the leasing agreements with Vornado were amended to eliminate the annual
	installment cap of $4,000,000 and we paid the accrued balance of leasing
	commissions of $
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_32178D278EE44EAAB92E1E312">
</A>
	40,353,000
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_32178D278EE44EAAB92E1E312_BCLEND">

<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:.7PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	ALEXANDER&#8217;S, INC. AND SUBSIDIARIES
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED
	FINANCIAL STATEMENTS (CONTINUED)
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_64037B9F697C44428941D559E">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	6.&#160;&#160;&#160; FAIR VALUE MEASUREMENTS
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_TS_94A5C2317D9E44AB8879BE651">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	ASC 820,
</FONT>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Fair
	Value Measurement and Disclosures
</FONT>
</I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	defines fair value and establishes a
	framework for measuring fair value.&#160; The objective of fair value is to
	determine the price that would be received upon the sale of an asset or paid to
	transfer a liability in an orderly transaction between market participants at
	the measurement date (the exit price).
</FONT>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#160;
</FONT>
</I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	ASC 820 establishes a fair value
	hierarchy that prioritizes observable and unobservable inputs used to measure
	fair value into three levels: Level 1 &#8211; quoted prices (unadjusted) in active
	markets that are accessible at the measurement date for assets or liabilities;
	Level 2 &#8211; observable prices that are based on inputs not quoted in active
	markets, but corroborated by market data; and Level 3 &#8211; unobservable inputs
	that are used when little or no market data is available.&#160; The fair value
	hierarchy gives the highest priority to Level 1 inputs and the lowest priority
	to Level 3 inputs. In determining fair value, we utilize valuation techniques
	that maximize the use of observable inputs and minimize the use of unobservable
	inputs to the extent possible as well as consider counterparty credit risk in
	our assessment of fair value.
</FONT>
</FONT>
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_TS_94A5C2317D9E44AB8879BE651_BCLEND">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_64037B9F697C44428941D559E_BCLEND">
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_418DCEE7F9C24BC5BD362C670">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Financial
	Assets and Liabilities Measured at Fair Value
</FONT>
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Financial assets measured at fair value on our consolidated
	balance sheets as of December 31, 2016 and 2015 consist of marketable
	securities, which are presented in the table below, based on their level in the
	fair value hierarchy, and an interest rate cap which fair value is
	insignificant, as of December 31, 2016 and 2015. There were no financial
	liabilities measured at fair value as of December 31, 2016 and 2015.
</FONT>
</FONT>
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_418DCEE7F9C24BC5BD362C670_BCLEND">
</A>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

</A>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Financial
	Assets and Liabilities not Measured at Fair Value
</FONT>
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Financial assets and liabilities that are not measured at
	fair value on our consolidated balance sheets include cash equivalents and mortgages
	payable.&#160; Cash equivalents are carried at cost, which approximates fair value
	due to their short-term maturities.&#160; The fair value of our mortgages payable is
	calculated by discounting the future contractual cash flows of these
	instruments using current risk-adjusted rates available to borrowers with
	similar credit ratings, which are provided by a third-party specialist.&#160; The
	fair value of cash equivalents is classified as Level 1 and the fair value of mortgages
	payable is classified as Level 2.&#160; The table below summarizes the carrying
	amounts and fair value of these financial instruments as of December 31, 2016
	and 2015.
</FONT>
</FONT>
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_52537F46ED824B499D381CA24_BCLEND">
</A>
</P>

	&nbsp;
</FONT>

</A>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	7.&#160;&#160;&#160; LEASES
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.25IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;">
	As Lessor
</FONT>
</U>
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-TOP:6.0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	We lease space to tenants in an office building and in
	retail centers.&#160; The rental terms range from approximately 5 to 25 years.&#160; The
	leases provide for the payment of fixed base rents payable monthly in advance
	as well as reimbursements of real estate taxes, insurance and maintenance
	costs.&#160; Retail leases may also provide for the payment by the lessee of
	additional rents based on a percentage of their sales. We also lease
	residential space at The Alexander apartment tower with one or two year lease
	terms.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">

<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_67FE71B1AF2343D3BADF026EF_BCLEND">
</A>
	% and
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_A3C96562129249698CCDCDACB">
</A>
	45
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_A3C96562129249698CCDCDACB_BCLEND">
</A>
	% of our total revenues in
	each of the years ended December 31, 2016, 2015 and 2014, respectively.&#160; No
	other tenant accounted for more than
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_A23F708E155F46A3932A7E685">
</A>
	10
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_A23F708E155F46A3932A7E685_BCLEND">
</A>
	% of our total revenues.&#160; If
	we were to lose Bloomberg as a tenant, or if Bloomberg were to be unable to
	fulfill its obligations under its lease, it would adversely affect our results
	of operations and financial condition. In order to assist us in our continuing
	assessment of Bloomberg&#8217;s creditworthiness, we receive certain confidential
	financial information and metrics from Bloomberg.&#160; In addition, we access and
	evaluate financial information regarding Bloomberg from other private sources,
	as well as publicly available data.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<H5 STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:13.7PT;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;FONT-WEIGHT:NORMAL;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;TEXT-DECORATION:NONE;">
	&nbsp;

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.7PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	In January 2016, we entered into a lease amendment with
	Bloomberg which extends the lease term related to
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_23E67B906DF7469A89187B801">

	192,000
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_23E67B906DF7469A89187B801_BCLEND">
</A>
	square feet of office
	space at our 731 Lexington Avenue property to be coterminous with the other
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_D7B7C00D29DE4A66B9F53230D">
</A>
	697,000
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_D7B7C00D29DE4A66B9F53230D_BCLEND">
</A>
	square feet of office
	space leased by Bloomberg through February 2029, with a ten-year extension
	option.&#160; In connection with the lease amendment, Bloomberg provided a $
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_40DDC58AFFC049E08821CDEB4">
</A>
	200,000,000
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_40DDC58AFFC049E08821CDEB4_BCLEND">
</A>
	letter of credit, which
	amount may be reduced in certain circumstances. We may draw on this letter of
	credit subject to certain terms of the lease amendment, including an event of
	default by Bloomberg.&#160; Upon execution of the lease amendment in January 2016,
	we paid an $
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_CEDCF09FEC154CDAA2B259454">
</A>
	8,916,000
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_CEDCF09FEC154CDAA2B259454_BCLEND">
</A>
	leasing commission of
	which $
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_2FFEB8EB89604BDC90E3D105E">
</A>
	7,200,000
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_2FFEB8EB89604BDC90E3D105E_BCLEND">
</A>
	was to a third party
	broker and $
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_5BFA155D43A04CE78222C0E39">
</A>
	1,716,000
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_5BFA155D43A04CE78222C0E39_BCLEND">

	was to Vornado.

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;">
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_C6BFAAE339E145598C6A8C2C3">

<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	8.&#160;&#160;&#160; STOCK-BASED
	COMPENSATION
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Our
	2016 Omnibus Stock Plan, which was adopted in May 2016 replacing the expiring
	2006 Omnibus Stock Plan, provides for grants of incentive and non-qualified
	stock options, restricted stock, stock appreciation rights, deferred stock
	units (&#8220;DSUs&#8221;) and performance shares, as defined, to the directors, officers
	and employees of the Company and Vornado, and any other person or entity as
	designated by the Omnibus Stock Plan Committee of our Board of Directors.&#160; As
	of December 31, 2016, there were
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_08B02DB104C8404F9FFCB2126">
</A>
	8,505
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_08B02DB104C8404F9FFCB2126_BCLEND">
</A>
	DSUs outstanding and
</FONT>
</FONT>
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_F1ED9C56792240E8B3CCAB642">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	498,376
</FONT>
</FONT>
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_F1ED9C56792240E8B3CCAB642_BCLEND">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	shares were available for future grant under the 2016 Omnibus Stock Plan.&#160; We
	account for all stock-based compensation in accordance with ASC 718.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	In
	May 2016, we granted each of the members of our Board of Directors
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_80FAD375E599485F874B4C351">
</A>
	203
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_80FAD375E599485F874B4C351_BCLEND">
</A>
	DSUs with a grant date
	fair value of $
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_FF2BCF102BD847A582E507B3B">
</A>
	56,250
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_FF2BCF102BD847A582E507B3B_BCLEND">
</A>
	per grant, or $
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_856ECD784214495B93C457FA6">
</A>
	450,000
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_856ECD784214495B93C457FA6_BCLEND">
</A>
	in the aggregate.
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_TS_EB509E716D7B41919926A8C57">
</A>
	The DSUs entitle the holders to
	receive shares of the Company&#8217;s common stock without the payment of any
	consideration. The DSUs vested immediately and accordingly, were expensed on
	the date of grant, but the shares of common stock underlying the DSUs are not
	deliverable to the grantee until the grantee is no longer serving on the
	Company&#8217;s Board of Directors.
</FONT>
</FONT>
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_C6BFAAE339E145598C6A8C2C3_BCLEND">
</A>
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_TS_EB509E716D7B41919926A8C57_BCLEND">
</A>

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;">
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_667C25923DBA4F94B08D70EE4">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	9.&#160;&#160;&#160; COMMITMENTS
	AND CONTINGENCIES
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.25IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:0PT;">
	Insurance
</FONT>
</U>
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	We maintain general liability insurance with limits of $
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_1D592EBDBCD34DEE88181A147">
</A>
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_263FC48130EA42EA889E99038">
</A>
	300,000,000
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_1D592EBDBCD34DEE88181A147_BCLEND">
</A>
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_263FC48130EA42EA889E99038_BCLEND">
</A>
	per occurrence and per
	property, and all-risk property and rental value insurance coverage with limits
	of $
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_0715FD93C4744095932D37321">
</A>
	1.7
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_0715FD93C4744095932D37321_BCLEND">
</A>
	billion per occurrence,
	including coverage for acts of terrorism, with sub-limits for certain perils
	such as floods and earthquakes on each of our properties.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Fifty Ninth Street Insurance Company, LLC (&#8220;FNSIC&#8221;), our
	wholly owned consolidated subsidiary, acts as a direct insurer for coverage for
	acts of terrorism, including nuclear, biological, chemical and radiological
	(&#8220;NBCR&#8221;) acts, as defined by the Terrorism Risk Insurance Program
	Reauthorization Act, which expires in December 2020.&#160; Coverage for acts of
	terrorism (including NBCR acts) is up to $
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_147CFBC3F991447A8EE2780A9">
</A>
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_E9A4E9ADCC324BFE8005E1F8D">
</A>
	1.7
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_147CFBC3F991447A8EE2780A9_BCLEND">
</A>
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_E9A4E9ADCC324BFE8005E1F8D_BCLEND">
</A>
	billion per occurrence and
	in the aggregate.&#160; Coverage for acts of terrorism (excluding NBCR acts) is
	fully reinsured by third party insurance companies and the Federal government
	with no exposure to FNSIC.&#160; For NBCR acts, FNSIC is responsible for a $
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_E1AE2746CC974A03B133867F6">
</A>
	348
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_E1AE2746CC974A03B133867F6_BCLEND">
</A>
	,000 deductible ($
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_F2A8CCFEA6864117B5EEB6CD5">
</A>
	293
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_F2A8CCFEA6864117B5EEB6CD5_BCLEND">
</A>
	,000 effective January 1,
	2017) and
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_4E685EDA8F8E4274895853B32">
</A>
	16
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_4E685EDA8F8E4274895853B32_BCLEND">
</A>
	% of the balance (
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_59764C29D59B492FA50388739">
</A>
	17
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_59764C29D59B492FA50388739_BCLEND">
</A>
	% effective January 1,
	2017) of a covered loss, and the Federal government is responsible for the
	remaining
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_4B5E587303494F899F13A4D2A">
</A>
	84
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_4B5E587303494F899F13A4D2A_BCLEND">
</A>
	% (
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_F03D8B1B9AC54CF4826FA310B">
</A>
	83
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_F03D8B1B9AC54CF4826FA310B_BCLEND">
</A>
	% effective January 1,
	2017) of a covered loss.&#160; We are ultimately responsible for any loss incurred
	by FNSIC.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	We continue to monitor the state of the insurance market
	and the scope and costs of coverage for acts of terrorism.&#160; However, we cannot
	anticipate what coverage will be available on commercially reasonable terms in
	the future.&#160; We are responsible for deductibles and losses in excess of our
	insurance coverage, which could be material.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Our mortgage loans are non-recourse to us and contain
	customary covenants requiring us to maintain insurance.&#160; Although we believe
	that we have adequate insurance coverage for purposes of these agreements, we
	may not be able to obtain an equivalent amount of coverage at reasonable costs
	in the future.&#160; If lenders insist on greater coverage than we are able to
	obtain, it could adversely affect our ability to finance our properties.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:0IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:0PT;">
	Rego Park I Litigation
</FONT>
</U>
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	On June 24, 2014, Sears Roebuck and Co. (&#8220;Sears&#8221;) filed a
	lawsuit in the Supreme Court of the State of New York against Vornado and us
	(and certain of our subsidiaries) with regard to space that Sears leases at our
	Rego Park I property alleging that the defendants are liable for harm Sears has
	suffered as a result of (a) water intrusions into the premises, (b) two fires
	in February 2014 that caused damages to those premises, and (c) alleged
	violations of the Americans with Disabilities Act in the premises&#8217; parking
	garage.&#160; Sears asserted various causes of actions for damages and sought to
	compel compliance with landlord&#8217;s obligations to repair the premises and to
	provide security, and to compel us to abate a nuisance that Sears claims was a
	cause of the water intrusions into its premises.&#160; In addition to injunctive
	relief, Sears sought, among other things, damages of not less than $4 million
	and future damages it estimated would not be less than $25 million. In March
	2016, Sears withdrew its claim for future damages leaving a remaining claim for
	property damages, which we estimate to be approximately $650,000 based on
	information provided by Sears. We intend to defend the remaining claim
	vigorously. The amount or range of reasonable possible losses, if any, is not
	expected to be greater than $650,000.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_667C25923DBA4F94B08D70EE4_BCLEND">
</A>
<FONT COLOR=RED STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT COLOR=RED FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#160;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.25IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-13.5PT;">
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_01511751FE124D189F5219C14">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<I>
<U>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:0PT;">
	Paramus
</FONT>
</U>
</I>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:13.5PT;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	In 2001, we leased 30.3 acres of land located in Paramus,
	New Jersey to IKEA Property, Inc. The lease has a purchase option in 2021 for
	$75,000,000. The property is encumbered by a $68,000,000 interest-only mortgage
	loan with a fixed rate of 2.90%, which matures in October 2018. The annual
	triple-net rent is the sum of $700,000 plus the amount of debt service on the
	mortgage loan. If the purchase option is exercised, we will receive net cash
	proceeds of approximately $7,000,000 and recognize a gain on sale of land of
	approximately $60,000,000. If the purchase option is not exercised, the
	triple-net rent for the last 20 years would include debt service sufficient to
	fully amortize $68,000,000 over the remaining 20-year lease term.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT COLOR=BLACK FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	In October 2015, the New York City
	Department of Finance (&#8220;NYC DOF&#8221;) issued a Notice of Determination to us
	assessing an additional $
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_34CDFAD15D9C4C9CB5A06C9E0">
</A>
	21,300
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_34CDFAD15D9C4C9CB5A06C9E0_BCLEND">
</A>
	,000 of transfer taxes
	(including interest and penalties as of December 31, 2016) in connection with
	the sale of Kings Plaza in 2012. We believe that the NYC DOF&#8217;s claim is without
	merit and intend to vigorously contest this assessment. We have determined that
	the likelihood of a loss related to this issue is not probable and, after
	consultation with legal counsel, that the outcome of this assessment is not
	expected to have a material adverse effect on our financial position, results
	of operations or cash flows.

</FONT>

	Our subsidiaries make contributions to certain
	multiemployer defined benefit plans (&#8220;Multiemployer Pension Plans&#8221;) and health
	plans (&#8220;Multiemployer Health Plans&#8221;) for our union represented employees,
	pursuant to the respective collective bargaining agreements.

	Multiemployer Pension Plans
</FONT>

</FONT>

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Multiemployer Pension Plans differ from single-employer
	pension plans in that (i) contributions to multiemployer plans may be used to
	provide benefits to employees of other participating employers and (ii) if
	other participating employers fail to make their contributions, each of our
	subsidiaries may be required to bear their pro rata share of unfunded
	obligations.&#160; If a participating subsidiary withdraws from a plan in which it
	participates, it may be subject to a withdrawal liability.&#160; As of December 31,
	2016, our subsidiaries&#8217; participation in these plans were not significant to
	our consolidated financial statements.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	NOTES TO CONSOLIDATED
	FINANCIAL STATEMENTS (CONTINUED)

<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">

<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</B>

</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_B18CDC70154140F38D6E2DA7A">
</A>
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;">
	11.&#160; EARNINGS PER SHARE
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	The
	following table sets forth the computation of basic and diluted income per
	share, including a reconciliation of net income and the number of shares used
	in computing basic and diluted income per share.&#160; Basic income per share is
	determined using the weighted average shares of common stock (including DSUs)
	outstanding during the period.&#160;
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_TS_5B950B636B3F4654B00FCAF81">
</A>
	Diluted
	income per share is determined using the weighted average shares of common
	stock (including DSUs) outstanding during the period, and assumes all
	potentially dilutive securities were converted into common shares at the
	earliest date possible.
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_TS_5B950B636B3F4654B00FCAF81_BCLEND">
</A>
	&#160;
	There were
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_BC3CCA0799B242E3A964CAC9F">
</A>
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_D32219196FA749F1B6E2C95B7">
</A>
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_3C804DD0813541A28BF910BEF">
</A>
	no
<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_3C804DD0813541A28BF910BEF_BCLEND">

<A NAME="ALEX10K2016_HTM_XBRL_CS_BC3CCA0799B242E3A964CAC9F_BCLEND">

	potentially dilutive
	securities outstanding during the years ended December 31, 2016, 2015 and 2014.

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:12.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.75IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-INDENT:-.75IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;">
	ITEM 9a.&#160; controls
	and procedures
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Disclosure
	Controls and Procedures &#8211; Our management, with the participation of our Chief
	Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer, have evaluated the effectiveness
	of our disclosure controls and procedures (as such term is defined in Rules
	13a-15(e) and 15d-15(e) under the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended)
	as of the end of the period covered by this Annual Report on Form 10-K.&#160; Based
	on such evaluation, our Chief Executive Officer and Chief Financial Officer
	have concluded that, as of the end of such period, our disclosure controls and
	procedures are effective.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Internal
	Control Over Financial Reporting &#8211; There have not been any changes in our
	internal control over financial reporting (as defined in Rule 13a-15(f) under
	the Securities and Exchange Act of 1934, as amended) during the fourth quarter
	of the fiscal year to which this report relates that have materially affected,
	or are reasonably likely to materially affect, our internal control over
	financial reporting.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>

<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	The
	management of Alexander&#8217;s, Inc., together with its consolidated subsidiaries
	(the &#8220;Company&#8221;), is responsible for establishing and maintaining adequate
	internal control over financial reporting.&#160; The Company&#8217;s internal control over
	financial reporting is a process designed under the supervision of the
	Company&#8217;s principal executive and principal financial officers to provide
	reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial reporting and the
	preparation of the Company&#8217;s financial statements for external reporting
	purposes in accordance with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States of America.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	As of
	December 31, 2016, management conducted an assessment of the effectiveness of
	the Company&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting based on the framework
	established in
</FONT>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Internal Control &#8211; Integrated Framework (2013)
</FONT>
</I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	issued by
	the Committee of Sponsoring Organizations of the Treadway Commission.&#160; Based on
	this assessment, management has determined that the Company&#8217;s internal control
	over financial reporting as of December 31, 2016 is effective.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	The
	Company&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting includes policies and
	procedures that pertain to the maintenance of records that, in reasonable
	detail, accurately and fairly reflect transactions and dispositions of assets;
	provide reasonable assurances that transactions are recorded as necessary to
	permit preparation of financial statements in accordance with accounting
	principles generally accepted in the United States of America, and that
	receipts and expenditures are being made only in accordance with authorizations
	of management and the directors of the Company; and provide reasonable
	assurance regarding prevention or timely detection of unauthorized acquisition,
	use, or disposition of the Company&#8217;s assets that could have a material effect
	on the Company&#8217;s financial statements.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	The
	effectiveness of the Company&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting as of
	December 31, 2016 has been audited by Deloitte &amp; Touche LLP, an independent
	registered public accounting firm, as stated in their report appearing on page
	57 of this Annual Report on Form 10-K, which expresses an unqualified opinion
	on the effectiveness of the Company&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting
	as of December&nbsp;31, 2016.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.2IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&#160;&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MSO-BORDER-SHADOW:YES;MSO-PADDING-ALT:31.0PT 31.0PT 31.0PT 31.0PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">

<EFX_AUDITORS_OPINION>
<A NAME="FIS_AUDITORS_OPINION_2"></A>
<DIV BCLPAGEBORDER STYLE="PADDING-TOP: 0IN; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0IN; WIDTH: 100%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0IN; PADDING-LEFT: 0IN">
<DIV BCLHEADER>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MSO-LINE-HEIGHT-RULE:EXACTLY;MSO-PAGINATION:WIDOW-ORPHAN NO-LINE-NUMBERS;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:.7PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
</DIV>
<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;TEXT-INDENT:.3IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	REPORT OF INDEPENDENT REGISTERED PUBLIC ACCOUNTING FIRM
</FONT>
</B>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.3IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	To the Board of Directors and Stockholders
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Alexander&#8217;s, Inc.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Paramus, New Jersey
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	We have audited the internal control over financial reporting of Alexander&#8217;s,
	Inc. and subsidiaries (the &#8220;Company&#8221;) as of December 31, 2016, based on
	criteria established in
</FONT>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	Internal Control&#8212;Integrated Framework (2013)
</FONT>
</I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	issued by the Committee of Sponsoring Organizations of the Treadway
	Commission.&#160; The Company&#8217;s management is responsible for maintaining effective
	internal control over financial reporting and for its assessment of the
	effectiveness of internal control over financial reporting, included in the
	accompanying Management&#8217;s Report on Internal Control over Financial Reporting.&#160;
	Our responsibility is to express an opinion on the Company&#8217;s internal control
	over financial reporting based on our audit.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	We conducted our audit in accordance with the standards of the
	Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States).&#160; Those standards
	require that we plan and perform the audit to obtain reasonable assurance about
	whether effective internal control over financial reporting was maintained in
	all material respects.&#160; Our audit included obtaining an understanding of
	internal control over financial reporting, assessing the risk that a material
	weakness exists, testing and evaluating the design and operating effectiveness
	of internal control based on the assessed risk, and performing such other
	procedures as we considered necessary in the circumstances.&#160; We believe that
	our audit provides a reasonable basis for our opinion.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	A company&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting is a process
	designed by, or under the supervision of, the company&#8217;s principal executive and
	principal financial officers, or persons performing similar functions, and
	effected by the company&#8217;s board of directors, management, and other personnel
	to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of financial
	reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external purposes in
	accordance with generally accepted accounting principles.&#160; A company&#8217;s internal
	control over financial reporting includes those policies and procedures that
	(1) pertain to the maintenance of records that, in reasonable detail,
	accurately and fairly reflect the transactions and dispositions of the assets
	of the company; (2) provide reasonable assurance that transactions are recorded
	as necessary to permit preparation of financial statements in accordance with
	generally accepted accounting principles, and that receipts and expenditures of
	the company are being made only in accordance with authorizations of management
	and directors of the company; and (3) provide reasonable assurance regarding
	prevention or timely detection of unauthorized acquisition, use, or disposition
	of the company&#8217;s assets that could have a material effect on the financial
	statements.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	Because of the inherent limitations of internal control over
	financial reporting, including the possibility of collusion or improper
	management override of controls, material misstatements due to error or fraud
	may not be prevented or detected on a timely basis.&#160; Also, projections of any
	evaluation of the effectiveness of the internal control over financial
	reporting to future periods are subject to the risk that the controls may
	become inadequate because of changes in conditions, or that the degree of
	compliance with the policies or procedures may deteriorate.&#160;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	In our opinion, the Company maintained, in all material respects,
	effective internal control over financial reporting as of December 31, 2016, based
	on the criteria established in
</FONT>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	Internal Control&#8212;Integrated Framework (2013)
</FONT>
</I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:NORMAL;">
	issued by the Committee of Sponsoring Organizations of the Treadway Commission.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	We have also audited, in accordance with the standards of
	the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (United States), the consolidated
	financial statements and financial statement schedules as of and for the year
	ended December 31, 2016 of the Company and our report dated February 13, 2017
	expressed an unqualified opinion on those financial statements and financial
	statement schedules.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	/s/ DELOITTE &amp; TOUCHE LLP
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE=CALIBRI,SANS-SERIF LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;">

<BR>

<P STYLE="BORDER:NONE;MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.25IN;">
<FONT STYLE="BORDER:NONE;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Earnings equals (i) income from continuing operations
	before income taxes, plus (ii) fixed charges, minus (iii) capitalized interest.
	&#160;Fixed charges equals (i) interest and debt expense, plus (ii) the portion of
	operating lease rental expense that is representative of the interest factor,
	which is one-third of operating lease rentals and (iii) capitalized interest.
</FONT>
</FONT>
</P>

	statement schedules of Alexander&#8217;s, Inc. and subsidiaries (the &#8220;Company&#8221;) and

<DIV BCLPAGEBORDER STYLE="PADDING-TOP: 0IN; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0IN; WIDTH: 100%; PADDING-RIGHT: 0IN; PADDING-LEFT: 0IN">
<DIV BCLHEADER>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TAB-STOPS:CENTER 3.0IN RIGHT 6.0IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>

<P ALIGN=RIGHT STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;">
	EXHIBIT
	31.1
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P ALIGN=RIGHT STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<EFX_CERTIFICATION>
<A NAME="FIS_CERTIFICATION"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;">
	CERTIFICATION
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.3IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:12.95PT;">
	I, Steven Roth, certify that:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:10.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:12.95PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.75IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; I
	have reviewed this Annual Report on Form&nbsp;10&#8209;K of Alexander&#8217;s, Inc.;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.75IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	2.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Based
	on my knowledge, this report does not contain any untrue statement of a
	material fact or omit to state a material fact necessary to make the statements
	made, in light of the circumstances under which such statements were made, not
	misleading with respect to the period covered by this report;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.75IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	3.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Based
	on my knowledge, the financial statements, and other financial information
	included in this report, fairly present in all material respects the financial
	condition, results of operations and cash flows of the registrant as of, and
	for, the periods presented in this report;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.75IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	4.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; The
	registrant&#8217;s other certifying officer and I are responsible for establishing
	and maintaining disclosure control and procedures (as defined in
	Exchange&nbsp;Act Rules&nbsp;13a&#8209;15(e) and 15d&#8209;15(e)) and internal
	control over financial reporting (as defined in Exchange Act Rules 13a-15(f)
	and 15d-15(f)) for the registrant and have:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:1.0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	a)&#160;&#160;&#160; Designed such disclosure controls and procedures, or caused such
	disclosure controls and procedures to be designed under our supervision, to
	ensure that material information relating to the registrant, including its
	consolidated subsidiaries, is made known to us by others within those entities,
	particularly during the period in which this report is being prepared;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:1.0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	b)&#160;&#160;&#160; Designed such internal control over financial reporting, or
	caused such internal control over financial reporting to be designed under our
	supervision, to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of
	financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external
	purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:1.0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	c)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Evaluated the effectiveness of the registrant&#8217;s disclosure
	controls and procedures and presented in this report our conclusions about the
	effectiveness of the disclosure controls and procedures, as of the end of the
	period covered by this report based on such evaluation; and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:1.0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	d)&#160;&#160;&#160; Disclosed in this report any change in the registrant&#8217;s internal
	control over financial reporting that occurred during the registrant&#8217;s most
	recent fiscal quarter (the registrant&#8217;s fourth fiscal quarter in the case of an
	annual report) that has materially affected, or is reasonably likely to
	materially affect, the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting;
	and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.75IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	5.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; The
	registrant&#8217;s other certifying officer and I have disclosed, based on our most
	recent evaluation of internal control over financial reporting, to the
	registrant&#8217;s auditors and the audit committee of the registrant&#8217;s board of
	directors (or persons performing the equivalent functions):
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:1.05IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.3IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	a)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; All
	significant deficiencies and material weaknesses in the design or operation of
	internal control over financial reporting which are reasonably likely to
	adversely affect the registrant&#8217;s ability to record, process, summarize and
	report financial information; and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0IN;MARGIN-LEFT:1.05IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.3IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	b)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Any fraud, whether or
	not material, that involves management or other employees who have a
	significant role in the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0IN;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-INDENT:0IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0IN;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-INDENT:0IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

</P>
<P ALIGN=RIGHT STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:RIGHT;">
<B>

<EFX_CERTIFICATION>
<A NAME="FIS_CERTIFICATION_2"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:0PT;">
	CERTIFICATION
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:10.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:11.0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:115%;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.3IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	I, Joseph Macnow, certify that:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LETTER-SPACING:0PT;LINE-HEIGHT:12.95PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.75IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	1.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; I
	have reviewed this Annual Report on Form 10&#8209;K of Alexander&#8217;s, Inc.;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.75IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	2.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Based
	on my knowledge, this report does not contain any untrue statement of a
	material fact or omit to state a material fact necessary to make the statements
	made, in light of the circumstances under which such statements were made, not
	misleading with respect to the period covered by this report;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.75IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	3.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Based
	on my knowledge, the financial statements, and other financial information
	included in this report, fairly present in all material respects the financial
	condition, results of operations and cash flows of the registrant as of, and
	for, the periods presented in this report;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.75IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	4.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; The
	registrant&#8217;s other certifying officer and I are responsible for establishing
	and maintaining disclosure control and procedures (as defined in
	Exchange&nbsp;Act Rules&nbsp;13a&#8209;15(e) and 15d&#8209;15(e)) and internal
	control over financial reporting (as defined in Exchange Act Rules 13a-15(f)
	and 15d-15(f)) for the registrant and have:
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:1.0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	a)&#160;&#160;&#160; Designed such disclosure controls and procedures, or caused such
	disclosure controls and procedures to be designed under our supervision, to
	ensure that material information relating to the registrant, including its
	consolidated subsidiaries, is made known to us by others within those entities,
	particularly during the period in which this report is being prepared;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:1.0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	b)&#160;&#160;&#160; Designed such internal control over financial reporting, or
	caused such internal control over financial reporting to be designed under our
	supervision, to provide reasonable assurance regarding the reliability of
	financial reporting and the preparation of financial statements for external
	purposes in accordance with generally accepted accounting principles;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:1.0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	c)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; Evaluated
	the effectiveness of the registrant&#8217;s disclosure controls and procedures and
	presented in this report our conclusions about the effectiveness of the
	disclosure controls and procedures, as of the end of the period covered by this
	report based on such evaluation; and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:1.0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	d)&#160;&#160;&#160; Disclosed
	in this report any change in the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial
	reporting that occurred during the registrant&#8217;s most recent fiscal quarter (the
	registrant&#8217;s fourth fiscal quarter in the case of an annual report) that has
	materially affected, or is reasonably likely to materially affect, the
	registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting; and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:.75IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	5.&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; The
	registrant&#8217;s other certifying officer and I have disclosed, based on our most
	recent evaluation of internal control over financial reporting, to the
	registrant&#8217;s auditors and the audit committee of the registrant&#8217;s board of
	directors (or persons performing the equivalent functions):
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:6.0PT;MARGIN-LEFT:1.0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	a)&#160;&#160;&#160; All significant
	deficiencies and material weaknesses in the design or operation of internal
	control over financial reporting which are reasonably likely to adversely
	affect the registrant&#8217;s ability to record, process, summarize and report
	financial information; and
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:1.0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;PAGE-BREAK-AFTER:AUTO;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:-.25IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	b)&#160;&#160;&#160; Any
	fraud, whether or not material, that involves management or other employees who
	have a significant role in the registrant&#8217;s internal control over financial
	reporting.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0IN;MARGIN-LEFT:.75IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-INDENT:0IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:0IN;MARGIN-LEFT:.75IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-INDENT:0IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>

<EFX_CERTIFICATION>
<A NAME="FIS_CERTIFICATION_3"></A>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:.25IN;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	CERTIFICATION
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<H1 STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;LETTER-SPACING:-.1PT;LINE-HEIGHT:12.0PT;TEXT-TRANSFORM:UPPERCASE;">
	Pursuant to Section 906 of the
	Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002
</FONT>
</B>
</H1>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	(Subsection
	(a) and (b) of Section 1350 of Chapter 63 of Title 18 of the United States
	Code)
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN-BOTTOM:.25IN;MARGIN-LEFT:0IN;MARGIN-RIGHT:0IN;MARGIN-TOP:0IN;TEXT-ALIGN:CENTER;">
<B>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:CHAR;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</B>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.45IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:LINE;">
	Pursuant to Section 906 of the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002 (subsections
	(a) and (b) of Section 1350 of Chapter 63 of Title 18 of the United States
	Code), the undersigned officer of
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	Alexander&#8217;s, Inc.
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:LINE;">
	(the &#8220;Company&#8221;), hereby certifies, to such
	officer&#8217;s knowledge, that
</FONT>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	:&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.45IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	&nbsp;
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.45IN;">
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	The Annual Report on Form
	10-K for year ended December 31, 2016
</FONT>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
</FONT>
</I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(the &#8220;Report&#8221;) of the Company
	fully complies with the requirements of Section 13(a) or 15(d) of the
	Securities Exchange Act of 1934 and the information contained in the Report fairly
	presents, in all material respects, the financial condition and results of
	operations of the Company.
</FONT>
</P>
<P STYLE="MARGIN:0IN;MARGIN-BOTTOM:.0001PT;TEXT-ALIGN:JUSTIFY;TEXT-INDENT:.45IN;">

	(a) and (b) of Section 1350 of Chapter 63 of Title 18 of the United States
	Code), the undersigned officer of

	Alexander&#8217;s, Inc.

<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;LAYOUT-GRID-MODE:LINE;">

</FONT>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">

	The Annual Report on Form
	10-K for year ended December 31, 2016
</FONT>
<I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
</FONT>
</I>
<FONT FACE="TIMES NEW ROMAN,SERIF" LANG=EN-US STYLE="FONT-SIZE:10.0PT;">
	(the &#8220;Report&#8221;) of the Company
